I’m actually currently working on designing a world that actually addresses that. While of course the characters dialogue and what not is in English, the actual languages that they speak are pretty much ancient languages like Latin and Celtic but modified to exclude sounds which include the lips.

For instance the word “Human” in Latin is “Humanum”, however when put into the Imperial language it becomes “Hunitis” and the Latin word for “Beast”, “Bestia”, becomes Destias. Now while this may sound strange there is a method to my madness, where the letters are replaced with ones that sound roughly familiar:

M’s are replaced with N’s or K’s
B’s are replaced with D’s
P’s are replaced with H’s
V’s are replaced with S’s or Z’s
F’s are replaced with T’s

I of course have other rules for translation, but I don’t even know how to begin explaining.
